The paper proposes a new model for object recognition tasks using Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) and Fully Connected SubNetworks (FCSNs). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the training and optimization of the model, which suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the use of FCSNs indicates that the paper could be related to neural networks and deep learning, which are covered in cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also proposes a new approach to improve the performance of CNNs, which could be related to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the experimental results involve classification tasks, which could be related to cs.CL (Computation and Language).
